<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>Blog Post Review Result - Rejected</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: #333;
      }
      .container {
        max-width: 600px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 20px;
      }
      .header {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 30px;
      }
      .content {
        margin-bottom: 30px;
      }
      .footer {
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 14px;
        color: #666;
      }
      .reason {
        background-color: #f8f8f8;
        padding: 15px;
        border-left: 4px solid #dc3545;
        margin: 20px 0;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="header">
        <h2>Blog Post Review Result</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <p>Dear <%= userName %>,</p>

        <p>
          We regret to inform you that your blog post "<strong
            ><%= blogTitle %></strong
          >" has been reviewed and could not be approved at this time.
        </p>

        <div class="reason">
          <p><strong>Reason for Rejection:</strong></p>
          <p><%= comment %></p>
        </div>

        <p>
          You are welcome to make the necessary revisions and submit your blog
          post again for review. Please ensure that your content adheres to our
          community guidelines and maintains academic integrity.
        </p>

        <p>
          If you need any clarification about the rejection reason or guidance
          on our content standards, please don't hesitate to contact our support
          team.
        </p>

        <p>
          Thank you for your understanding and commitment to creating valuable
          content for our academic community.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="footer">
        <p>Need help? Contact us at <%= supportEmail %></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
